NOTE: GOES satellite data do not contain coordinate information. Therefore it must be provided by the user. Luckily, coordinate files exist, but you must manually download them.

GOES coordinate files can be accessed from links at this URL: https://www.star.nesdis.noaa.gov/atmospheric-composition-training/satellite_data_goes_imager_projection.php

Either download all available files linked on that page or you may download the file corresponding to the specific satellite (as of 2026, GOES-18 or GOES-19) and sector (Full Disk or CONUS).

You should then create a link to these files in your run directory when running the regridder program.
